---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro'

const bookingHref = 'https://cal.com/builtbywin/20-min-ai-sprint-fit-call'
---

<BlogLayout
  title="work with me"
  description="A four-call AI app sprint for business owners who want to launch an app and keep building it with AI"
  pathSegments={[{ name: 'work-with-me', href: null }]}
  backHref="/ston"
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>work-with-me/</h1>
    <p class="page-description">from scratch to a shipped app with ai coding</p>
  </header>

  <section class="hero">
    <h2>go from an idea to a live app you can keep building with ai</h2>
    <p>
      no coding background required. over four 1:1 calls, we will set up your ai coding
      environment, launch your app on the web, and ship one useful feature for your business.
    </p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={bookingHref} data-work-with-me-cta="hero">
      book a free 20-minute call →
    </a>
    <p class="availability">4 calls · $1,500 · three founding-client spots · mac required</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what you will get</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>an ai coding and development environment configured on your mac</li>
      <li>a working starter app deployed at a public URL after our first call</li>
      <li>one useful business feature working end to end and shipped online</li>
      <li>a repeatable workflow for continuing to build the app yourself</li>
      <li>async help between calls when you get stuck</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what to expect</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>call 1—set up and launch:</strong> configure your ai coding tools and developer
        environment, create the app, and deploy it to the web. after this call, you can begin
        prompting and building.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>calls 2–4—scope, build, and ship:</strong> choose one useful feature for your
        business and work together to get it working end to end. you can make progress between
        calls, then bring back anything that is blocked, broken, or ready for review.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>if you need more help:</strong> add another call whenever you need to get unstuck
        or want help shipping the next part.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>founding-client requirements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>you use a mac that you can install developer tools on</li>
      <li>you have an app idea, internal tool, or useful business feature in mind</li>
      <li>you are willing to work hands-on during the calls</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
      no coding experience is required. the founding sprint is mac-only so i can provide one
      reliable setup while the offer is new.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>why me</h2>
    <p>
      i am a <a href="/ston/resume">software engineer with almost a decade of experience</a>. i
      have built production-quality apps for myself and for big tech companies.
    </p>
    <p>
      through <a href="https://zerostack.builtby.win/">zero stack</a>, i have taught other
      business owners how to build with ai. their projects include
      <a href="https://cfwproductions.com/">cfw productions</a>,
      <a href="https://flash.handlworks.com/">flash</a>, and
      <a href="https://import-bonds.reddata.io/">import bonds</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      i am a problem solver and a builder, so i will help you build exactly what you need as
      cheaply as possible—and teach you how to be your own developer. you do not need a new bill.
      you need a new skill.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what happens next</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        book a free call and tell me about your business, the work that takes too long, and where
        your customers or staff get stuck.
        <details>
          <summary>some ideas</summary>
          <ul>
            <li>upload files for customers to download</li>
            <li>collect customer requests in one place</li>
            <li>show customers project status or reports</li>
            <li>track jobs, requests, or files for your staff</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
      </li>
      <li>we discuss what would be useful for your business and whether the sprint is a good fit</li>
      <li>if it is, i send the scope, call schedule, and payment link</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="final-cta">
    <h2>want your app live after our first call?</h2>
    <p>bring the idea. we will set up the tools and get it onto the web together.</p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={bookingHref} data-work-with-me-cta="footer">
      book a free 20-minute call →
    </a>
  </section>
</BlogLayout>
<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-work-with-me-cta]').forEach((link) => {
    link.addEventListener('click', () => {
      window.posthog?.capture('work_with_me_cta_clicked', {
        cta_location: link.getAttribute('data-work-with-me-cta'),
        offer: 'ai_app_sprint',
        price_usd: 1500,
      })
    })
  })
</script>

<style>
  .page-header,
  .hero,
  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-header h1,
  h2 {
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability,
  .muted {
    color: var(--color-term-fg-muted);
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul,
  ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: disc;
  }

  ol {
    list-style: decimal;
  }

  li + li {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  details {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  details ul {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  summary {
    width: fit-content;
    color: var(--color-term-link);
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-term-link);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .primary-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-term-bg);
    background: var(--color-term-dir);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .primary-cta:hover,
  .primary-cta:focus-visible {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
  }

  .muted {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .final-cta {
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-term-bg-lighter);
  }

  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    .primary-cta {
      display: block;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
